node.text: Wes Studi breaks down his most iconic characters. Hit the link in bio for the full vid.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by GQ on July 22, 2021 tagging @tietztietz, @willwelch, @michael_schmelling, @frontgeneralstore, @schottnyc, @cartier, and @chromeheartsofficial. May be an image of 1 person.

node.text: When #WesStudi broke through in Dances With Wolves and The Last of the Mohicans, he was cast as a terrifying villain. But for many in the Native community, he was a hero channeling decades of righteous anger. For the August issue of GQ, Tommy Orange tells the story of an overlooked icon who forever changed the way Indigenous people are depicted onscreen. Head to the link in bio to read the story and see all the photographs by @michael_schmelling.
